Louie has been a little under the weather this week and super clingy. All he wants is me. As I was getting ready this morning, he was whining while I was getting ready because he wanted me to hold him (not because he wasn’t well; he’s better, he just wanted me). And that could be quite annoying especially for someone who needs a lot of alone time, like me, but motherhood definitely makes you think about your needs differently. It reminds you so much more about how some things will not last forever. A season comes along & instead of coming back next year.. it actually never returns. Once that season is gone, it’s gone forever. One day, he won’t be this little. One day, I won’t be able to hold him. One day, I won’t see him reaching up for me. One day, he won’t think I’m hilariously funny (that’s for sure). So, now, when I think “I just need a second to myself” … an almost immediate thought follows .. “he won’t always be this little or want me this much”. And, while I think we do need to take care of ourselves (in whatever way that looks / makes sense for you & your situation) because parenthood can be overwhelming and hard and just.. A LOT .. I am grateful for that perspective because it reminds me to really relish in these moments, even when they could be a little frustrating or annoying. So, give me all the arms outreached, give me all the hugs. Even all the whines as he follows me around while I try to get ready 😄 His love gives me so much happiness and I hope mine always does the same for him. #motherhood #perspective

We made it to #Puglia yesterday and have been spoiled by sunshine, beautiful weather, delicious food, stunning views and the loveliest company! This morning, we explored Ostuni, the White City. It’s wild that it dates back to 600 BC! (Matera, which is close by, dates back even further 🤯). It’s feels so nice to explore new places with my two favorite guys - Louie is doing so well and traveling like a champ! 🥹 Let me know if you’ve been to Puglia and where we need to go (restaurants, towns, beaches etc)! We’re all ears! (keep in mind we have a stroller haha) 🤍 my outfit details are here for anyone interested: https://liketk.it/4870g @shop.ltk #traveloutfit #ostuni #puglia #pugliagram

Instagram vs. Reality yesterday in #Alberobello (swipe; what you might not be able to see is rain, wind and my soaking wet shoes and bottom of my dress) 😂 I can’t let y’all believe our trip has been all rainbows and sunshine. Louie got sick in his car seat en route to the airport this morning. I made many wrong turns and experienced baptism by fire as a driver on Italian roads. I don’t think my heart rate was below 100 anytime I was behind the wheel, ha. John had to take a sick day thanks to food poisoning. BUT, traveling is such a privilege and the benefits far outweigh its challenges, especially for little ones (even if they won’t remember the specific place later on). I truly could not be more grateful for the highs and lows of our trip. We did have so much fun overall! Can’t wait to tell you more about #Puglia and what we got up to. Leave me your questions below! I’ll be working on a blog post answering them all next week!

Last week, I spent a couple of hours shooting content for the blog in Notting Hill so, naturally, I treated myself to a post-shoot mooch about in Westbourne Grove, just a short walk from Portobello Road. Here are a few of the spots that I’m always bound to pop into when I’m in the area: • @sohohome for an always fresh and modern take on home interiors
• @sezane showcases gorgeous, colorful seasonal clothing that are well made and long-lasting
• @daylesfordfarm for a healthy lunch or a great selection of organic cheeses, juices and teas, fresh produce and classic homewares
• @wildathearthq for gorgeous blooms to cheer up a friend or your home; the owner is also super passionate about rescuing dogs so I love supporting her business
• @bodyism for the absolute best iced honey latte and açaí bowl [they also offer a wellness membership if you’re a local and want to join!]
• @aesopskincare for the most gorgeous smelling soaps
• @me_andem for an absolutely stunning selection of items with beautiful feminine detailing
• @loveshackfancy for the ultimate girly girl and pink lover
• @thehagenproject strong cup of coffee for either sit-in or on-the-go
• @ottolenghi for anyone with a sweet tooth - they have the best pastries and desserts [and don’t miss the cook books!]
.
Of course, I’m probably missing a few and this truly only scratches the surface of all the great spots in Notting Hill but that’s a good start for anyone who may be wanting to explore the area. Let me know if you want a Part 2 or what neighborhood you’d like me to highlight next! Taking requests in the comments below! xx

Belgravia in Bloom is one of many floral, botanical and horticultural events happening this week in #London. Long-standing and much loved florists in the neighborhood (tagged below) create floral displays adorning squares and storefronts to raise awareness for the overall theme. This year, in partnership with @londonwildlifetrust, Belgravia in Bloom’s theme is ‘Into the Wild’ in support of their mission to boost biodiversity and inspire Londoners to connect with nature. There are loads of events going on all over the neighborhood of #Belgravia this week so be sure to head over to @belgravia_ldn for a full list of happenings now through the 28th of May! 🙌🏼
.
FLORAL DISPLAY LOCATIONS:
🦚 Motcomb Street: ‘Wonders of the Wild’ by @neillstrain 
🐘 Halkin Arcade on Motcomb Street: ‘Safari in the City’ .by @neillstrain 
🪸 Newson’s Yard on Pimlico Road: ‘An Underwater Wilderness’ by @moysesstevens 
🐼 Elizabeth Street: ‘Belgravia’s Bamboo Bears’ by @moysesstevens 
🦒 Eccleston Yards (in between Eccleston St & Elizabeth St): ‘Eccleston Explorers’ by @moysesstevens 
🦋 Kinnerton Street: ‘Orchids & Butterflies’ by @judithblacklockflowerschool 
.
And there are loads more floral displays adorning storefronts like @bayleyandsage, @peggyporschenofficial and @lessenteurs 🌸

#Marylebone is one of the chicest neighborhoods in #London, filled with great shopping, activities and dining. Here’s how we recently spent a lovely out here:
9AM: Start the day with coffee at @thehagenproject or @shop.monocle 
10AM: Spend some time browsing @dauntbooks - an independent Edwardian bookshop (that originally specialized in travel books). 
11AM: Pop into @ottolenghi for a sweet treat (many locations across #London - this highly praised chef is a must-try whilst in the city!)
12PM: Shop along Marylebone High Street’s lovely boutiques like @kjs_laundry , @bashparis, @me_andem (and soon, a new @sezane location!)
1PM: Head to @chilternfirehouse for lunch (ideally on the terrace if it’s a lovely day!)
3PM: Spend the afternoon taking in the masterpieces at @wallacemuseum (both their permanent collection and current exhibition “Portraits of Dogs” are worth seeing!)
5PM: Grab a glass of wine and nibbles from @2850marylebone 
7PM: End the day with a quintessential pub dinner at @thegrazinggoatw1 

There’s plenty more to love about this area, but this is more than enough to get you started😉 Follow us for more of our #London favorites… and be sure to let us know in the comments what questions you want us to answer about traveling to our favorite city! 🇬🇧 #londontravel #lifeinlondon

BOOKMARK FOR YOUR NEXT TRIP TO NYC 🍎 
.
🏨 STAY:  @conradnymidtown 
I wouldn’t say staying in Midtown is my first choice BUT I honestly loved it for this trip, in particular, and I LOVED this hotel for so many reasons. The staff was incredibly kind and helpful. The location is 2 blocks from the subway and 4 blocks from Central Park and equally as close to some of my favorite shopping spots. The bed felt like a cloud and I felt like a Queen staying there. I also really loved that it was in Midtown but far enough away from the craziness of Time Square (I could see it on my walks but never went down there which was amazing 🤣)
.
🍔 EAT: here are some of my favorite spots in the city, although I def need to refresh this list next time I come as these are mostly old faves —
• San Ambroeus - this is where we ate for lunch; the Cacio E Pepe rivals Roman restaurants, dare I say 👀
• The Smith - a classic
• Butcher’s Daughter - great for brunch, get there early
• Jack’s Wife Freda - believe the hype
• Totto Ramen - so great, especially when it’s cold out
• Boucherie West Village - lovely French restaurant
• Via Carota - amazing Italian!
.
WHAT TO DO:
• grab picnic bits from Whole Foods or a salad from SweetGreen and have a picnic in Central Park at sunset 
• see a Broadway show (use TodayTix to book 🙌🏼)
• pick a neighborhood to explore like the Upper West Side, Soho, West Village, Chelsea, etc - it’s the best way to see the city IMO
• go shopping if that’s your thing (I went to Nordstrom and the shopping center around Columbus Circle but you can literally shop in lots of different neighborhoods) 
• get up early and walk around to enjoy the city before it wakes up (I know “it never sleeps” but you can truly enjoy a calmer NYC if you get up early 😊)
.
And, as always, download the CityMapper app to navigate the city. It’s always my best friend when I’m traveling 🙌🏼
.
Leave YOUR #NYC faves before for anyone visiting soon! ✈️😘 #traveltips #newyorkcity #thebigapple

If you found out you were pregnant and (for whatever reason) you don’t feel ready, this is your reminder that it’ll all be okay. You will shift and pivot. Things will feel hard sometimes but the rewards far and beyond outweigh them.
.
If you found out you were pregnant and you felt feelings that were outside of what you see in movies, you’re not alone. It can come with an array of feelings. And it doesn’t mean you don’t appreciate the blessing that it is. It’s okay. You’re not alone. And you are going to be okay. I promise.🤍
.
If you are about to become a boy mom … this is just one example of how they can so easily and naturally melt your heart with how pure and precious they can be.
.
This video and these words were so much of what I had wished I had read or could have seen when I found out I was pregnant with Louie. I’m proud of myself for how I’ve grown through the experience — really allowing myself to shed this idea of how life “should” go and challenging myself to define that for myself and really settling into that. It’s still a work in progress, there’s still quite a bit of de-conditioning to do there but I have made progress. This video is such a gift — a true testament to how much love, growth, satisfaction, and pure joy can be experienced when we allow ourselves to embrace the things in life that take us by surprise 🤍 #motherhood #boymom #hearttalks

THE FALL 🍂 I have always prided myself in being a ‘positive’ person. Over the years, at different points in time, my friends and other people in my life have told me just how admirable and inspiring my strength during hard times was to them.
.
So, after moving to the UK in 2020, and my life started to change in every way possible [in addition to the entire world changing simultaneously], it was really confusing to me just how much I struggled mentally. I couldn’t pull myself out of my emotional depths every time something unexpected happened, something didn’t go the way I had hoped, or something popped up that felt overwhelming. I was falling heavily into victim consciousness, limiting beliefs, and self-sabotage as well as ruminating over every. little. thing. I didn’t feel like I met any of it with the same mental fortitude I once could. It was so disorienting. I felt like everything - my life and who I was - was crumbling from underneath me and in front of me.
.
My thoughts were full of sadness and negativity but, worse than that, I was letting them completely run the show and dampen day after day. Soon, hopelessness set in along with an extreme lack of motivation. I couldn’t see my way out of it but I was desperate to find a way.
.
First, I sought out professional help and got on a medication to help elevate my mood so I can actually make something of the day. But, I wanted to do more and figure out what might be underneath, what the ultimate cause might have been, how to find it, and what could actually help that didn’t involve taking medicine ... not that there is any judgement around medication. I was just genuinely curious. How can I get back to myself? Or at least figure out how to step into this new version of me? So, I let my curiosity take the lead and started learning about just how powerful our minds are and how the way we CHOOSE to respond to our thoughts can completely change our life. I’m excited to share that there’s something brewing behind the scenes that will shed light on all of the things I’ve been exploring. A new era for Alyson Haley is coming ... stay tuned ✨ #mentalhealth

❤️🎄 LONDON at CHRISTMAS BUCKET LIST 🎄❤️
✨ Check out the lights and installations! They’re literally all over the city but here’s a few to favorite: 
• Regent Street, Oxford Circus, Burlington Arcade, Bond St [seen here]
• Covent Garden, Seven Dials, Neals Yard
• Berkeley Square, South Molton & Mount Street in Mayfair
• Elizabeth and Motcomb St in Belgravia
• Sloane Square, follow Sloane St all the way up and make your way to Harrods
… plus so many more! Honestly just walk everywhere!! 
⛸️ Ice skating at Somerset House, Canary Wharf, Battersea Power Station, and Winter Wonderland 
❤️ Meander through the festive Christmas markets along the Southbank [my fave!], Trafalgar Square, Leicester Square and Covent Garden
📸 Get snaps in front of the Christmas trees in Covent Garden, Trafalgar Square, or Somerset House
🍷 Bundle up, grab a mulled wine, and enjoy the light trail at Kew Gardens 
🎁 Send traditional British hampers home to family [or find other gifts to bring home] from the historic Fortnum & Mason
🎶 Find a Christmas carol service or concert to attend at Westminster Abbey, St. Pauls Cathedral, or Royal Albert Hall [check out VisitLondon.com for a list and links to book!]
🍗 Devour a festive meal at @daphneslondon, @the_ivy_collection, @coppaclub, @34Mayfair, or @dallowayterrace to name a few! (Book ahead ALWAYS!)
🔥 Warm up for some mulled wine, a pint or a Sunday Roast, at cozy pub like @thealfredtennyson, @thegrazinggoatw1, @thebarleymowmayfair, or @thegeorgepublichouse
🎡 If you’re going with kids or you’re a kid at heart, check out Winter Wonderland in Hyde Park [opening 11/17!]
.
I’ve long said that there’s nowhere that beats London at Christmas and it always brings a smile to my face when people say they’re finally coming to see it for themselves! I hope this list (while short as there is so much more to do and see) helps make it the best experience during your holiday season! ENJOY! 🫶🏼😘 p.s. the city is bussyyyyy this time of year so book as much ahead as you can!
.
#travelreel #londonatchristmas #christmasinlondon #whattodoinlondon #londonreels

POV: You’re living in your dream place abroad but your parents, back home, are getting older and you wish you could see them with your littles more often. 
.
When I fell in love with London, I became very aware that my heart would always be in a constant state of longing. I always want to be in it or close to it. It’s still surprising to me how deeply you can love and feel drawn to a place almost the same way that we love certain people. The layers of nuance to that deepened when I met @johnmartin_ but still lived in Florida, and deepened again when I had Louie but on the reverse end. While I always want to be in the UK, I also love being back but not because I love the place but because of the deep love of the people I’ve left there. To see them play and interact with Louie, a living, breathing extension of my heart, is something I relish in and love to see, and wish I could see more often, especially as my Dad gets older. 
.
All that to say, I don’t think this heart ache, regardless of which place I’m currently in, will ever fade. I’ll always wish I could merge both places, both realities, somehow … and I’m so grateful to be here, in my hometown, this Christmas to watch endless amount of magic unfold amongst so many of my favorites 🫶🏼 (also, how wild is it that Mitch did NOT wear neon to greet us at the airport?? he MUST have seen my post about it 😆😆)
.
#christmas2023 #magicalchristmas #homeforchristmas #floridachristmas

🔖 BOOKMARK FOR FUTURE —
.
📍 @laplanduk in Ascot, Berkshire, UK
💰 £59-139 plus a booking fee
💌: Sign up for their emails to know when tickets go on sale (usually early spring) & do not wait to book as they always sell out!
🦌: Activities include gingerbread making with Mrs. Claus, toy making with the elves, letter writing to Santa at his post office, ice skating if you so choose, visiting Santa’s reindeer as well as a meeting with the big man himself (who looks so incredibly real 👌🏼) … plus you literally feel like you’re in the North Pole ❄️🌲
.
John and I had a great time but loved it mostly because of how magical Louie thought it all was. It was so well done and you get so much out of the experience for the amount of money you spend. Highly recommend if you ever find yourself in England at Christmas 🥰

🔖 BOOKMARK FOR FUTURE DISNEY TRIPS 🏰 The Magic Kingdom being called the “most magical place on Earth” has never carried as much weight for me as it did after seeing it all through Louie’s eyes. He had such a great first experience at Disney and we can’t wait to take him back in the future! 
.
I’ll be putting a blog post together for anyone planning a trip with what we packed, where we stayed, and tips but here are a few quick takeaways (I’ll elaborate on these in the blog post, as well):
.
🧞‍♂️ Genie+ (their new FastPass system) is so worth it! It will minimize time spent waiting in lines and maximize the number of experiences you do in a day
☀️ Best time to come: November - April 
💦 Bring a refillable water bottle and snacks in with you 
👟 Comfortable shoes are a must!
✨ Keep expectations low and go with the flow
📱 Utilize the MyDisneyExperience app as much as possible and set up what you can before your trip
🥗 If you want anything remotely healthy, make sure you book a lunch / dinner reservation in advance
💗 Have someone in your party wear something easy to spot (Mitch enthusiastically volunteered himself to wear neon orange)
🏰 Absolutely do not miss the fireworks at the end of the night 
.

2023: the year i felt both lost and found ✨
.
this year, I reached my lowest of lows mentally and professionally but slowly found my way back to hope, possibility, positivity, dreaming and, most importantly, myself. i have let fear stand in my way a lot since moving here and this was the year i told myself to stop & that it’s time to step into my power and forget whoever can’t handle the real me … and I can’t wait to share more of me with you in 2024. i appreciate you sticking with me through all of the up’s and downs and inconsistency. i have always said this, but it’s true.. i feel so lucky to have you all as my community because you truly are such kind and supportive people.
.
quick recap:
❄️ JAN: overcome with fear and failure but got myself outside as much as possible 
🎂 FEB: celebrated my birthday in one of the places that brings me the most peace, the Cotswolds
🎈MAR: celebrated our gorgeous 2-year-old
😭 APR: finally sought help for my mental health (I was crying everyday, multiple times a day, taking hours long naps most days and feeling sad and hopeless everyday)
✈️ MAY: traveled to Italy for some sunshine and a change of scenery (Puglia is beautiful if you’ve ever thought about going)
🌿 JUN: lived slow, offline and outside in the park as much as possible and I’m convinced it was one of the most healing things i could have done for my mental health
🍎 JUL: ventured to NYC for a little work trip and also melted 
🧘🏻‍♀️ AUG: i did a lot of self-discovery this year … challenged myself to explore alternative ways of healing inner child wounds and triggers & studied both astrology and human design
🏡 SEP: moved house … just down the street in Windsor 
📸 OCT: got back into my style blogging groove and launched the development phase of two new projects
🍗 NOV: celebrated turkey day with framily 
🎄DEC: enjoyed endless magical moments
